article.headline: Mississippi Valley St 66, Central Arkansas 51
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Standford Speech scored 14 points and all but one Mississippi Valley State player scored as the Delta Devils dropped Central Arkansas 66-51 on Wednesday night. Ronald Alexander and Michael Clark each added 10 for Mississippi Valley State (3-6), which had a difficult shooting night but held an eight-point lead at halftime and was never challenged. Alexander also contributed 12 rebounds. Durrell Nevels and Mitch Rueter led Central Arkansas (4-7) with 11 points apiece. The Delta Devils forced 17 turnovers while committing 10, but struggled from the field. Mississippi Valley State hit 37 percent of its field goals and 73 percent of its free throws.
